  abstract  = "How is political violence gendered? We connect the traditional political violence literature{\textquoteright}s emphasis on categorizing attacks to the gender and politics literature{\textquoteright}s analysis of the barriers to women{\textquoteright}s political participation. Our framework separates gendered political violence into three elements. Gendered motives appear when perpetrators use violence to preserve hegemonic men{\textquoteright}s control of politics. Gendered forms emphasize how gender roles and tropes differentially shape men{\textquoteright}s and women{\textquoteright}s experiences of violence. Gendered impacts capture the subjective meaning-making processes that occur as different audiences react to political violence. This approach offers researchers and policymakers greater analytic precision regarding how political violence is gendered.",
